{
  "texts": [
    "Within b(s) → s(d)ν ν transitions, we consider the branching ratios of B+ → K + ν ν, K + → π + ν ν and K L → π 0 ν ν.",
    "For B + → K + ν ν we use the average B(B + → K + ν ν) exp B(B + → K + ν ν) SM = 2.8 ± 0.8, (3.3)which combines the recent experimental analysis of Belle-II [41] with previous searches of this mode (as reported in [41]), using the SM prediction in [42].",
    "For the analogous processes in s → d transitions, we use the experimental measurements given in [43,44] and the SM predictions in [45].",
    "The theory expressions for all these observables in terms of SMEFT WCs are given in appendix A.6.The last ∆F = 1 observable we consider is the branching ratio of the radiative decay B → X s γ.",
    "For the experimental value, we use the current world average of B exp sγ = (3.32 ± 0.15) × 10 -4 [46], while for the SM and NP theory contributions we closely follow [47]."
  ]
}